# Implementation Plan - AI-Powered Study Buddy

Build a premium, AI-driven study tool that helps students simplify complex topics, summarize notes, and practice with quizzes/flashcards.

## Project Architecture

The application will follow a modern Full-Stack architecture:

- **Frontend**: Next.js App Router for a hybrid (SSR/CSR) experience.
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS for a premium, responsive UI.
- **Animations**: Framer Motion for interactive elements like flashcard flips.
- **Backend**: Next.js API Routes (Edge/Serverless) to interact with the AI model.
- **AI Engine**: Google Gemini API (model: `gemini-1.5-flash` for speed, `gemini-1.5-pro` for complex logic).
- **Database**: MongoDB (via Mongoose) to store user profiles, study sessions, and history.

```mermaid
graph TD
    Client[Next.js Frontend] -->|API Request| Backend[Next.js API Routes]
    Backend -->|Prompt| Gemini[Google Gemini API]
    Backend -->|Store/Fetch| DB[(MongoDB)]
    Gemini -->|JSON/Text| Backend
    Backend -->|Response| Client
```

## Proposed Folder Structure

```text
/
├── app/                  # Next.js App Router files
│   ├── api/              # Backend API routes
│   │   ├── explain/      # "Explain it Simply" endpoint
│   │   ├── summarize/    # "Smart Summarizer" endpoint
│   │   └── generate/     # Quiz/Flashcard generation
│   ├── components/       # Reusable UI components
│   │   ├── ui/           # Headless UI/Custom primitives
│   │   ├── flashcards/   # Flashcard specific components
│   │   └── layouts/      # Dashboard/Main layouts
│   ├── dashboard/        # Main app view
│   ├── globals.css       # Tailwind & Global styles
│   └── page.tsx          # Landing page
├── lib/                  # Utility functions & shared config
│   ├── gemini.ts         # Gemini SDK initialization
│   ├── db.ts            # MongoDB connection
│   └── utils.ts          # Helper functions (clsx, tailwind-merge)
├── types/                # TypeScript interfaces
├── public/               # Static assets
└── package.json
```

## Step-by-Step Implementation

### Phase 1: Foundation
1. [NEW] Initialize Next.js project with Tailwind and Framer Motion.
2. [NEW] Configure `.env` for Gemini API Key and MongoDB URI.
3. [NEW] Initialize Gemini SDK client in `lib/gemini.ts`.

### Phase 2: "Explain it Simply" Tool
1. [NEW] Create `app/api/explain/route.ts` to handle AI explanations based on difficulty.
2. [NEW] Build Interactive Chat/Input UI in `app/components/ExplainTool.tsx`.

### Phase 3: Smart Summarizer
1. [NEW] Create `app/api/summarize/route.ts` (handle text and basic PDF parsing).
2. [NEW] Build Summarizer UI with copy-to-clipboard/save features.

### Phase 4: Quiz & Flashcard Generator
1. [NEW] Create `app/api/generate/route.ts` to generate JSON-formatted flashcards and MCQs.
2. [NEW] Build `FlashcardContainer` and `Flashcard` components with Framer Motion flip animations.

### Phase 5: Persistence
1. [NEW] Connect MongoDB.
2. [NEW] Create schemas for `Note` and `QuizHistory`.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- [ ] Test API routes using `curl` or Postman to ensure Gemini returns valid JSON responses.
- [ ] Unit tests for prompt construction logic in `lib/prompts.ts`.

### Manual Verification
- [ ] Verify flashcard flip animation smoothness.
- [ ] Test different difficulty levels for the "Explain it Simply" module.
- [ ] Check responsive design on mobile/desktop.
- [ ] Validate PDF upload and text extraction (MVP: text paste first).
